         <div xml:lang="en" type="translation" xml:space="preserve"><p>
            <milestone unit="line" n="1"/>He[liod]oros, son of Didymos, the son of Hephaistion, of the 
            <term target="SosikosmioshokaiAlthaieus">Sosicosmian tribe and of the Althaean deme</term>, to 
            Stotoetis, son of Stotoetis, greetings. <milestone unit="line" n="3"/>I acknowledge that I have sold to you a white 
            male camel, which has not shed its first teeth, branded on its right haunch with a 
            <app type="BGU"><lem resp="BL I 47, written as σγμμα on the papyrus"><foreign xml:lang="la">Sigma</foreign></lem></app> and a 
            <app><lem resp="The word παράσημον is usually used in the papyri to signify the ensign on the prow of a ship. As it is dependent upon κεχαραγμένον an artificial marking such as the letters and the burn mark on its chest seems more consistent, but it is possible that a birthmark may be what is intended, cf. LSJ παράσημον A II b.">distinguishing mark</lem></app> on the same haunch and on the 
            right of its neck a 
            <app type="BGU"><lem resp="Cf. BL I 47, written as σγιμα on the papyrus"><foreign xml:lang="la">Sigma</foreign></lem></app> and on 
            its chest a burn mark <milestone unit="line" n="8"/>and I have received from you the price agreed upon of six hundred 
            and eighty <term target="touargurioudrachmai">silver drachmas</term>, (=) 680 drachmas, and 
            <term target="bebaioseinpasebebaiosei">I shall guarantee (the sale) to you with every 
                guarantee</term>.
            <milestone unit="line" n="11" rend="break"/>Year 23 of Imperator Caesar Tit[us]Ael[ius Hadri]anus An[toninus] Augustus 
            Pius <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>.
        </p></div><div type="bibliography"><listBibl><bibl/></listBibl></div>
